"GA ASSISTANCE STANDARDS\n\nISSUE DATE: 04/2026\n\nMFIP, SNAP, MSA, HSP:\nNo provisions.\n\n\nGA:\nPeople who live in a licensed residential facility (including all residents of the Minnesota Sex Offender Program), receive Housing Support, or receive substance use disorder treatment services are eligible for the GA personal needs allowance. See 0020.24 (Personal Needs Allowance), 0013.15.12 (GA – Basis – Placement in a Facility), and 0013.15.54 (GA Basis – Drug/Alcohol Addiction).\n\nPay the personal needs allowance to the client or their authorized representative.\n\nResidents of homeless or family violence shelters, and people with drug or alcohol addiction who live in the community and are not receiving substance use disorder treatment services, are eligible for the full GA basic needs standards. See 0013.15.54 (GA Basis – Drug/Alcohol Addiction).\n\nAll other GA recipients are eligible for the full GA basic needs standard:\n\nELIGIBLE PEOPLE\n\n\t\n\nMONTHLY STANDARD\n\n\n\n\nOne adult living alone\n\n\t\n\n$360.50\n\n\n\n\nOne adult living with parent(s) or an ineligible spouse\n\n\t\n\n$360.50\n\n\n\n\nMinor or emancipated child not living with parent, stepparent, or legal custodian\n\n\t\n\n$360.50\n\n\n\n\nMarried couple with no children\n\n\t\n\nEach eligible unit member receives $360.50\n\nPREVIOUS REVISIONS\n\nDate\tNotes\n03/2026\tManuals Moratorium - removes DWP language for the DWP repeal, reviews DHS language, updates language of GRH to HSP, reinserts bold.\n10/2025\tThe assistance standard for GA recipients living in the community increases to $360.50 effective 10/1/2025.\n10/2024\tThe assistance standard for GA recipients living in the community increases to $350 effective 10/1/2024. This revision also simplifies and clarifies the language used to identify who is eligible for a personal needs allowance instead of the community standard.\n12/2014\tRemoved WB.  This program was suspended 12/1/14.\n09/2012\tupdate Food Support and FS to Supplemental Nutrition Assistance Program (SNAP) and FSET to SNAP E&T throughout. No policy was changed.\n\nReport this page"